r%20a%20chimney%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221877%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hand-lighting%20charcoal%20inside%20a%20grill%20with%20a%20lighter%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6290ed5714f0020018100d03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221407%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArrange%20balled-up%20newspaper%20under%20your%20charcoal%20and%20light%20it%20with%20a%20long%20lighter%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20chimney%20starter.%3Cp%3EGlasshouse%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20chimney%20starter%2C%20another%20reliable%2C%20yet%20simple%20option%20for%20starting%20a%20charcoal%20grill%20is%20the%20newspaper%20method.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Place%20newspaper%20under%20the%20grill%20grate.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Ball%20up%20newspaper%20and%20place%20it%20wherever%20you%20wish%20to%20place%20your%20charcoal.%20If%20you%20plan%20to%20have%20multiple%20heat%20zones%2C%20place%20the%20newspaper%20in%20each%20location%20charcoal%20will%20be.%20Sprinkle%20a%20bit%20of%20cooking%20oil%20on%20the%20newspaper%20to%20help%20it%20ignite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Arrange%20the%20charcoal%20around%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Use%20enough%20charcoal%20to%20cover%20the%20newspaper%20sufficiently%20while%20still%20allowing%20airflow%20to%20encourage%20ignition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Light%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Find%20a%20piece%20of%20exposed%20newspaper%20and%20light%20it%20with%20a%20long%20lighter.%20Remember%20to%20light%20your%20newspaper%20in%20every%20zone%20you%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Wait%20for%20the%20charcoal%20to%20ignite.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20will%20take%20a%20bit%20longer%20than%20it%20would%20with%20a%20charcoal%20chimney%20but%20the%20charcoal%20should%20all%20ignite%20within%20about%2015%20minutes.%20Keep%20your%20grill%20open%20to%20let%20oxygen%20feed%20the%20fire.%20You're%20ready%20to%20grill%20once%20your%20charcoal%20is%20grayish-white.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22With%20lighter%20fluid%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20start%20a%20charcoal%20grill%20with%20lighter%20fluid%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20experts%2C%20this%20is%20the%20least%20recommended%20of%20the%20three%20charcoal%20grill%20starting%20methods.%20Not%20only%20can%20it%20be%20dangerous%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20affect%20the%20taste%20of%20your%20food%20if%20not%20executed%20properly.%20Snider%20brothers%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BMany%20brands%20of%20lighter%20fluid%20are%20known%20to%20contain%20harmful%20chemical%20compounds%20that%20don't%20break%20down%20easily%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20they%20may%20end%20up%20in%20your%20food%20and%20potentially%20even%20make%20your%20food%20taste%20bad.%20For%20the%20same%20reason%2C%20they%20also%20suggest%20avoiding%20instant-light%20charcoal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20this%20be%20your%20only%20option%2C%20though%2C%20Groark%20reassures%20us%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20you%20allow%20%5Bthe%20lighter%20fluid%5D%20to%20burn%20off%20to%20that%20amber%20glow%2C%20you%20will%20taste%20nothing%20but%20that%20classic%20charcoal%20flavor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Arrange%20charcoal%20on%20the%20grill.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPlace%20your%20charcoal%20in%20your%20preferred%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Douse%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20pile(s)%20in%20lighter%20fluid.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Use%20approximately%201%2F4%20cup%20of%20lighter%20fluid%20per%20pound%20of%20charcoal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Light%20with%20a%20long%20lighter.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Let%20the%20lighter%20fluid%20soak%20in%20for%20about%2030%20seconds%20first%2C%20and%20back%20up%20when%20lighting%20in%20case%20of%20a%20flare-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Let%20the%20charcoal%20burn%20until%20it%20is%20gr